===============================================
				What is Exception ?
===============================================

=> Un-expected and unwanted situation  in the program execution is called as Exception.
=> Exception will disturb normal flow of the program execution.
=> When Exception occured program will be terminated autometically.
   
   Note: As a programmer we are responsible for programs graceful termination.
=> To achieve graceful termination we need to handle the exceptions occured while program execution. 
=> The process of handling Exception is called as Exception Handling.
=> The main aim of Exception Handling to achieve graceful termination of the program.

===> In Java we have so many predefined exceptions.

Ex: 
		ArithematicException
		NullPointerException
		FileNotFoundException
		SQLException 

=====================
Exception Hierarchy
=====================
=> In this hierarchy, Throwble is the root class

  1. Throwble 
     1.1 Exception
		1.1.1 -> Checked Exception
		1.1.2 -> Un-checked Exception
	 1.2 Error

Q.Difference beween Exception and Error ?
=========================================

---> Exception can be handled but Error can not be handled.

Exception Types
===============

Exceptions are devided into 2 types

1.Checked Exception : Will be identified at compile time.(occures at run time)
	Ex: IOException, FileNotFoundException, SQLException etc...

2.Un-checked Exception : Will occure at run time.(compiler can not identify these exception)
   Ex: NullPointerException, ArithmethicException etc........































































